data.title: Preparations for the unveiling of Sir Anerood Jugnauth's statue are in full swing, with various teams working diligently to finalize all...
data.meta_description:
19 likes, 0 comments - 3news.info on June 14, 2024: "Preparations for the unveiling of Sir Anerood Jugnauth's statue are in full swing, with various teams working diligently to finalize all the necessary details.

The official ceremony is set to take place tomorrow, Saturday, June 15, at 15:00 at the Caudan Waterfront.

The event will be attended by Prime Minister Pravind Jugnauth and several other esteemed guests.

Sir Anerood Jugnauth, a prominent figure in Mauritian politics, served as both Prime Minister and President, leaving a lasting impact on the nation. The unveiling of his statue is a fitting tribute to his legacy and contributions to Mauritius.".
